2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper uses computer vision techniques to reconstruct the tactile shape of objects from tactile imprints. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes algorithms for object localization and identification, which can be considered as AI techniques. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper may use machine learning techniques for object recognition and localization. 
5. cs.ROBOTS (Robotics and Automation): The paper's focus on tactile sensing and manipulation makes it relevant to the Robotics and Automation sub-category.
